<p><b>What is the difference between CyberArk and cyber security?</b> What is CyberArk used for? CyberArk uses proven cybersecurity measures like access control, two-factor authentication, encryption, firewalls, and VPNs to protect your company against hacks, attacks, and other cybercriminal activities.</p>
<p><b>What is ISPSS CyberArk?</b> CyberArk Identity Security Platform Shared Services (ISPSS) provides a single unified platform for managing user privileges, managing access to organizational resources, automatically rotating access credentials, recording access sessions, and auditing user activities.</p>
<p><b>What is CyberArk and how does it work?</b> CyberArk is a security device utilized to guard privileged accounts through password management. It maintains records of passwords at an organization and guarantees password change over all the administrations through cryptographic control.</p>
<p><b>Is CyberArk considered MFA?</b> CyberArk Identity features an adaptive multi-factor authentication (MFA) solution. You can customize the solution based on your security needs.</p>
<p><b>What is the difference between Pam and PIM?</b> PIM centers on the access a user possesses, focusing on identity and access and detailing pre-existing permissions. PAM, conversely, emphasizes managing and monitoring access as users seek it. In essence, while PIM delineates granted permissions, PAM handles on-the-fly access requests to resources.</p>
